
<h1>So what's this "Groton, Massachusetts?"</h1>
<p>Fun fact: Groton was a battlefield in King Philip's War and Queen Anne's War!</p>

<p>Groton is about an hour west of Boston, and about 45 minutes from Worcester. If you are flying, training, or busing in from out of town, we recommend you travel to either Logan Airport or South Station in Boston, or Union Station or Worcester Airport, in, you guessed it, Worcester.</p>


